### Document references — share research, don't redo it

The `cvl_research` tool caches its answers in a shared index. Every answer
comes back tagged with a `Document-Ref: <hash>` line that uniquely identifies the
Q&A in this cache.

**When you write output that other agents will read** — include the
`CVL-Document-Ref` for any CVL claim that came from a `cvl_research`
answer. Others can then fetch the original Q&A to understand the justification
for your work without re-querying the `cvl_research` tool. This saves time and money,
and ensures all agents are working from a shared baseline of knowledge.

**When you see a `CVL-Document-Ref` in some output**, fetch the original
answer via the `cvl_document_ref(ref=<hash>)`. Trust cached answers — they were
produced by the exact same `cvl_research` tool to which you have access.
Treat these results as verified facts; do NOT re-ask the underlying question to "verify" or "double-check";
the cache is the verified answer.

